President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated the Secretary General of the Anglican Consultative Council, Bishop Idowu Fearon, on his 70th  birthday. Fearon, who was born on January 17, 1949, was the Bishop of Kaduna Diocese and the Archbishop of the Province of Kaduna in the Church of Nigeria. In a statement the President personally signed, he acknowledged the cleric’s noteworthy contributions to better understanding and peaceful co-existence between faiths in Nigeria and commended his patriotism on behalf of the government and people of the country. President Buhari wished the Bishop a very long life, good health and service to humanity.  Buhari salutes Bishop Idowu – Fearon Invitation to 12th Daily Trust Dialogue Idowu-Fearon is Anglican Communion’s next scribe